# Google Sheets API Configuration for RSVP form submissions
# 
# 1. Create a service account in Google Cloud Console:
#    - Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#    - Create a new project or select existing
#    - Enable Google Sheets API
#    - Create a service account and download the JSON key file
#
# 2. Share your Google Sheet with the service account email:
#    - Open your Google Sheet
#    - Click "Share" and add the service account email (from the JSON file)
#    - Give it "Editor" permissions
#
# 3. Set these environment variables:
#    - GOOGLE_SHEETS_CREDENTIALS: Paste the entire JSON content as a single-line string
#      OR set it to the file path of your credentials JSON
#    - GOOGLE_SHEET_ID: Your Google Sheet ID (from the URL)
#
# Sheet URL format: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/SHEET_ID/edit
# Example Sheet ID: 1Pkl0ZtshbOWe-aNHQceRRDNhfarLWpN2h-6WJLBMCek

# Paste your service account JSON credentials here (as a single-line JSON string)
# Or use a file path: GOOGLE_SHEETS_CREDENTIALS_PATH=/path/to/credentials.json
GOOGLE_SHEETS_CREDENTIALS={"type":"service_account","project_id":"your-project","private_key_id":"...","private_key":"...","client_email":"...","client_id":"...","auth_uri":"...","token_uri":"...","auth_provider_x509_cert_url":"...","client_x509_cert_url":"..."}

# Your Google Sheet ID (extract from the sheet URL)
GOOGLE_SHEET_ID=1Pkl0ZtshbOWe-aNHQceRRDNhfarLWpN2h-6WJLBMCek
